(42, 6, 13, 49, 2, 20, 20, 'whom also he named apostles', 'Apostolic Foundation Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of the apostles in establishing the early church. Luke 6:13 identifies the chosen apostles, while Ephesians 2:20 emphasizes their foundational importance in the church''s structure.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 13, 40, 19, 28, 28, 'whom also he named apostles', 'Connection of the Twelve Apostles', 'This connection highlights the significance of the twelve apostles chosen by Jesus in Luke 6:13, who are later referenced in Matthew 19:28 as sitting on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel. Both passages emphasize the role of these twelve in the establishment of Jesus'' ministry and future authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
